    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD is a pristine example of Japanese engineering, featuring the legendary 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. Maintained to exacting standards, the powerplant delivers linear boost across the rev range with optimal compression levels. The chassis retains its factory-spec double-wishbone suspension and Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring the surgical handling precision the FD is renowned for. All original components remain intact, from the vacuum lines to the intercooler ducting, with zero structural fatigue or oxidation. This is a collector-grade specimen offering a visceral, analog driving experience in its truest mechanical form.",
